  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Lateral Icky Shuffle uses the agility ladder as a visual target to train lateral rhythm, inside-outside foot placement, and re-acceleration timing. The athlete moves through the boxes with clean contacts, controlled posture, and enough rest to keep every rep crisp.","setup":["Lay the agility ladder flat and remove tripping hazards.","Show one slow walk-through rep before speed is allowed.","Start tall with eyes forward, arms ready, and feet just outside the first box."],"execution_steps":["Step through the ladder using the assigned foot pattern.","Keep contacts light, posture tall, and arms coordinated with the feet.","Finish the ladder cleanly, decelerate under control, and walk back for the next rep."],"coach_cues":["Eyes up.","Fast but clean.","Step, do not stomp.","Own the pattern before speed."],"athlete_cues":["Stay tall.","Light feet.","Hit every box clean.","Slow down if your feet get messy."],"breathing_cues":["Breathe naturally; do not hold breath to move faster."],"quality_gate":["No missed boxes for one full pass","Posture stays tall","Speed increases only after the pattern is clean"],"common_faults":["Looking down the entire time","Skipping boxes unintentionally","Heavy flat-foot contacts","Torso folding or twisting to chase speed"],"stop_signs":["Tripping on the ladder","Repeated missed contacts","Athlete cannot decelerate after the finish"]}'::jsonb,
